# ----- Database (Postgres — Supabase in production) -----
# DATABASE_URL is a Postgres connection string.
#   • Local dev: your Supabase connection string (or a local Postgres).
#   • Serverless (Netlify): use Supabase's connection-POOLER URL
#     (Supavisor, transaction mode, port 6543) — NOT the direct 5432 one.
# See DEPLOY-NETLIFY.md for the full walkthrough.
# Example: postgresql://postgres.<ref>:<password>@aws-0-<region>.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres
DATABASE_URL=

# ----- AI: DeepSeek (OpenAI-compatible) -----
# Leave DEEPSEEK_API_KEY empty to use the built-in mock interpreter; set a real
# key to switch to live DeepSeek. NEVER commit the real key — for deployments,
# set it in the host's environment-variable settings, not in a file.
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=
DEEPSEEK_BASE_URL="https://api.deepseek.com"
